the end product in most cases is the classic sedimented blood sample with the rbc 's at the bottom , the buffy coat of platelets and wbc 's ( lymphocytes/granulocytes ( pmn 's , basophils , eosinophils/monocytes ) in the middle and the plasma on top .

giving blood : apheresis , in which you get your blood back , lets you donate these clotting blood cells to help those in need

